rlm-reset-kkp

Reset the Kitty Keyboard Protocol (KKP) by emitting the escape
sequence `ESC [ >u` to stdout.

Registered as a `precmd` zsh hook, so it runs automatically
before each prompt is drawn. Its purpose is to recover from
terminal applications (e.g. claude, neovim) that enable KKP via
`ESC [ >1u` and exit without restoring the previous mode,
which otherwise leaves keystrokes like Ctrl-C visible as raw
sequences such as `9;5u` at the prompt.

Safe to call manually if a terminal is stuck in KKP mode.
Takes no arguments.
